title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare Limited Edition Sig Sauer Pro 9mm
postcontent:
I picked this up one week ago, I got it for a good deal, brand new, and bought it because it was what I wanted and couldn't pass it up at the time. Following up on the pistol after purchasing it, I came to know that the gun was one of the 5,000 or so that was created for a South African Police force by special order, this order was then canceled after the pistols were assembled per spec in their German factory. 

The difference lies within the slide safety as well as the short tac trigger being preinstalled. The trigger is available from Sig Sauer aftermarket for Pro series pistols, but this one was fitted at the factory, as well as the slide safety (a bonus if you're a safety nut like me). 

There are exactly 13 mags down the pipe of this pistol, which equates to 130rds through it. The pistol has not been holstered, was cleaned and lubed accordingly prior to shooting, and has was cleaned within hours of shooting last weekend. 

Considering the pistol is not fully broken in, the groupings and feel of the firearm are quite impressive out of the box. I'd have NO problem keeping this, but more expenses have arisen for me and my wedding come May, so, my toys go first, unfortunately. 

C&C or Permit to Purchase are required upon purchase, as well as a valid MN driver's licence.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ruger Security Six 2 3/4" 357 Magnum SS
postcontent:
$600 OBO, OBO!!!! This is a highly collectable Ruger Security Six 2 3/4" barrel 357 Magnum in Stainless Steel. This gun is in 99% condition, I say 99% as it is used but not much!!! No rust, scratches, or any other issues. It is flawless.

When I say highly collectable, first off it was made in 1975, this was the first year Ruger made this gun in Stainless Steel, also this is a PRE-WARNING revolver. In 1977 Ruger started put warning stamps on the barrel stating to read owners manuel etc... before using the gun. My gun has no warning, lastly it is the snub nose version made with a 2 3/4" barrel, these are alot harder to come by as the production numbers on these length barrels were very limited. It has adjustable sights as well. Try and find a 2 3/4" Pre warning in this condition, you wont, I searched two years before I found this one and it was a fluke, they are just not out there for sale???

I have a nice pair of Hogue Grips on the gun and I also have the original wooden grips, the original grips are mint condition. This gun has been fired very little and lockup is super tight and the trigger in single action is crisp, so crisp and light it is amazing. One of the best pistols I have ever owned and fired. Selling it to fund another project!

Lastly this gun comes with a handmade leather holster, this holster was special made for this gun and the two combine for a excellect carry piece.
This gun also comes with two speed loaders and some ammo.

I will accept reasonable offers on this gun package. Additional pictures available upon request.
